cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about video-based person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses different methods for temporal modeling, which involves machine learning techniques such as attention and recurrent neural networks, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper proposes a new attention generation network, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, since the paper deals with surveillance and camera networks, it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
